commit.message: Bump version

Adwaita-Auto: a variant that can be changed on runtime

We use QPlatformTheme to give us what variant we should use. This way we can
update it on runtime and change variants on GNOME setting changes.
Update configuration on palette change
Don't watch changes on DBus interface we no longer have

adwita[.h|colors.h|renderer.h]: Use ADWAITAQT_MAIN_EXPORT

This is so that we can distinguish between building and/or using
adwaitaqt[6].dll and adwaitaqt[6]priv.dll, so that we can properly build, link
and link to them.

adwaitabusyindicatordata.h: Use ADWAITAQT_EXPORT

This is so that we control more carefully how we export and import from
adwaitaqt[6]priv.dll.

adwaitaqt_export.h: Add ADWAITAQT_MAIN_EXPORT

Since we have two library DLLs being built in the build process, define a
macro ADWAITAQT_MAIN_EXPORT to control how we export/import from the
adwaitaqt[6].dll, similar to the previous update for building
adwaitaqt[6]priv.dll.  This will enable items that link to adwaitaqt[6].lib
to link successfully on Visual Studio builds.

adwaitaqt_export.h: Define ADWAITAQT_EXPORT on Windows accordingly

...to whether we are building adwaitaqt[6]priv.dll, because we need to have it
set as __declspec(dllimport) in order to import items from the
adwaitaqt[6]priv.lib correctly, for items that use things from
adwaitaqt[6]priv.lib.

This is part of the fixes needed to link adwaitaqt[6].dll et al successfully on
Visual Studio.
Use QT_PLUGINS_DIR for Qt6 so we can override the path where plugins get installed
Use QT_PLUGINS_DIR for Qt6 so we can override the path where plugins get installed
Bump version to 1.4.1
